ugh the section also mentions `field:password` tag which I should verify is properly captured.\n\nLooking at s2 more closely, the hints include `gridSize`, `入力画面表示`, `確認画面非表示`, `注記マーク`, and `multicol_mode` — all of which appear to be present in the source material. For s3, the hints cover `hint.tag`, `タグファイル`, `内部構造`, and `部品一覧`, with the file path `/WEB-INF/tags/widget/field/hint.tag` adequately represented by the `hint.tag` hint.\n\nI'm noticing a small gap in the attribute table legend — the knowledge file captures the symbol meanings but drops the parenthetical clarification \"(指定しても効果なし)\" that explains what \"無効\" actually means in practice. It's minor detail, but it does add useful context about what happens when an invalid attribute is specified.\n\nLooking more closely at the code sample, the source labels it \"実装成果物(サーバ動作)\" to indicate it's the server implementation, but the knowledge file omits this label. Since the spec already states that local and server behavior are identical, this label is just a navigation marker and doesn't affect the actual content. Overall the documentation looks solid.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13095,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13095,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dbbac993-8c07-4f53-925b-71f198b789cd","uuid":"433af249-7a42-4884-bc51-7f6d84ed67fc"}
